{
  "texts": [
    "a and b are hyperparameters indicating the step size.",
    "In the first stage, the h values for each episode are fine-tuned with the samples of the support set (Eq. 5).",
    "In the second stage, the h parameters are updated using the samples of the query set (Eq. 6).",
    "These stages are repeated for each episode and the h parameters are updated by the stochastic gradient descent (SGD) method according to the derivative of the total Loss (L) value.",
    "Here, L is calculated by comparing the model predictions (Y) with the ground truth.At meta-testing stage, the learnt h parameters are used as a starting point for the given support and query sets."
  ]
}